Input Values\: vm.requester.email - The email address from the prior step result htmldocument - THe email body text from the prior result ca34f695-600c-41ed-a382-fa89540c6fb3.54be0c86-adad-4c57-aca4-56b40a75b5a9.description=
This operation checks whether a string matches another string, using a specific matching rule. The "toMatch" input is the string that is checked for matching the "matchTo" expression. 

Inputs\:
    matchType - The type of match to perform.
Valid values\: Exact Match, Contains, Contains Once, Does Not Contain, Match All Words, Match No Words, Regex
Default value\: Exact Match
    toMatch - The string that is checked for matching.
    matchTo - The string to match against.
Example\: If "matchType" is “RegEx”, the "matchTo" input is a regular expression such as\: ^-?\d+(([\.,]\d+)?)+$. 
    ignoreCase - Specifies whether to ignore case when matching or not.
Valid values\: False, True
Default value\: False

Results\:
    returnResult - This is the primary output. It contains the string "Matches" if the "toMatch" string matches the "matchTo" string. Otherwise, it contains the string "Does Not Match".  

Responses\:
    success - The operation completed as stated in the description.
    failure - The operation completed unsuccessfully.

Generate Run URL - Generates an href HTML link that contains a URL to the run history report for the current run.

Inputs\:
    variablename  - The name of the flow variable where the result should be stored.
Default value\: IC_ReportURL
    displaytext - The text to display for the href link. 
Default\: "Run History Report Available Here"

Results\:
    result - The untagged URL to the run report for the current run.
Example (with default values)\: IC_ReportURL ,Run History Report Available Here

Input Values\: vm.requester.email - The email address from the prior step result htmldocument - THe email body text from the prior result ca34f695-600c-41ed-a382-fa89540c6fb3.description=Purpose\: This flow creates a virtual volume on the 3Par, presents it to the cluster hostset and partitions the disk. Prerequisites\: 1. A physical cluster must have been provisioned successfully within one subscription. 2. A cluster name must have been created and stored in the CCLUSTER table 3. A 3Par hostset must have been created for the cluster. The hostset name must equal the cluster name. Implementation\: The following steps are performed sequentially in the OO flow\: 1. Create Virtual Volume createvv -tpvv -spt 304 -hpc 8 -snp_cpg ${CPG} -pol stale_ss,no_one_host,zero_detect ${CPG} ${diskName} ${diskSize}g 2. Present volume to hostset createvlun -f ${diskName} ${diskNumber} set\:${clusterName} 3. Verify that LUN has been created successfully and presented to hostset\: showvlun -host set\:${clusterName} 4. Add disk details to DISKDRIVE table in InfraDB 5. Update quorum disk size as visible CSA property 6. Partition disk which has been identified previously as “primary” server. The primary server is identified once for the cluster subscription because shared cluster disks are added to InfraDB with a relation to a single server which is the primary server. ca34f695-600c-41ed-a382-fa89540c6fb3.e34e8d44-fad0-4de1-bf8c-34190729be77.description=This flow will format and mount initial and additional datadisks to virtual and physical servers. The inputs are\: server.os Mandatory - should contain 'win' in case of windows, and '2008' or '2012' to make a difference between those two isAdditional Mandatory - should be 'True' if the disk that is added is not the first initial datadisk, but an additional one lun.wwname Only required for additional Linux datadisks disk.filesystem Only required for Linux servers server.hostname Madatory disk.mountpoint Not used at the moment. Can be used later to specifiy a mountpoint. See memo in the flow. disk.size Mandatory for Windows (All servers), and for Linux virtual servers isVirtual Mandatory - should be 'True' if the server is a virtual server. False for physical servers
